8:
Or else the pleas of the weak will
always fall on deaf ears.
23:
I'm sorry, Memram... I couldn't save
anyone...
25:
What're you saying? You, Essla, are
the pride of the Vestaâ€”
27:
Fight on, Memram... The weak... will

36:
Vesta, proud warriors! Stay close to
me!
47:
You intend to release the winged
ones onto the surface?
50:
Yes, and then that'll give us the
chance to rescue the trapped Vesta.
But we can't do this alone.
61:
Yeah, you can tell whether we're
lying by reading our... Oudo, was it?
69:
But... You seem fearful to carry out
this plan.
73:
I guess an Oudo tells you more than
just how sincere someone is. Kinda
embarrassing, really...
77:
...Yeah, we're pretty scared. There's a
lot of risk involved, but we want to
do everything we can to help.
88:
The fate of the Vesta is in your
hands. We will help you.
104:
It's almost time, Memram. Are you
ready?
111:
Lady Memram, leader of the Vesta.
First, allow me to take this
opportunity to apologize.
114:
The former Resistance took
advantage of the Vesta's
Oudo-reading abilities.
116:
I sincerely apologize for the
abhorrent treatment your people
received...
120:
Raise your eyes, King of Man. There
is no need to apologize for the past.
127:
I also must inform you that it will be
very difficult for the Vesta to return
home.
131:
Yes. The heroes have told me of the
abyss and how Pandemonium is
already merging with this world.
135:
...If you are already aware of that,
perhaps it would be best if we
explained everything to you.
140:
Restoration efforts are underway in
the Silver Woods, but are a
temporary measure at best.
142:
The day will come when we must
leave this land... Or, rather, this
world. Rebuilding ourselves while
helping your people relocate
presents an extreme challenge.
146:
I promise that we will not abandon
the Vesta.
148:
But realistically, our people are not
in a position to be able to share
resources.
153:
She's telling the truth. Use your
powers to confirm her sincerity, if
you wish.
157:
No.
I believe her, and there is no need
for my people to return to our old
lands.
160:
Our place of origin is but a frozen
wasteland now. We can call it our
home no longer.
162:
The Vesta will be the first to press on
to a new land that we can call home.
166:
...Are you saying you will go ahead
and establish a foothold for us over
there?
169:
We have no intention of taking any
space by force. However, we will
serve as an intermediary for you, if
you wish.
172:
Much like the Hero of the Red Soup
was for us.
176:
A hero... You're not referring to the
one next to you, are you?
180:
Indeed. I think we all know who she
speaks of.
184:
Hero of the... Red Soup? How
interesting.
186:
My, I can't lose focus for a moment!
It won't do to let everyone surpass
me.
190:
To surpass one another... and strive
for new heights together...
195:
Wh-why are you using your power
now?
200:
I'm not entirely sure what this feeling
is.
204:
But I will go forth and do everything I
can for the people that require a
helping hand!
